place_description: KB’s Coffee is located just off of Hwy 74 and offers a large selection of specialty coffee and drinks! Hungry for a muffin or pastry? We have that too! Stop by and see us, you will be glad you did.

reviews_data.review_text: Nice place to hang out, have a cup of coffee,do a little work. Kaleb, owner and barista.

Best coffee in Monroe hands down. Would venture to say best coffee shop in Union County. If you like really sweet barely there coffee, stay with Dunkin. If you like coffee with personality and great service, give Kbs a try!
My fav. Coffee spot!!!!
Great coffee

Small coffee shop that can seat two to four people at ten varies tables and comfortable chairs. Plus bar seating. Fast friendly and professional staff. Not a huge offering of snacks. Good coffee drink menu. Lots of parking. We will return again. Worth a try.
The atmosphere is so cozy and homey! Really cute coffee shop and wonderful barista's

I finally had the opportunity to stop by this awesome coffee shop in Monroe NC, I ordered a frappe "Monty's Holy Grail" and it was superb! The atmosphere was everything you want in a coffee shop plus more, the customer service was outstanding, very friendly and the owner told me their specials and gave me great suggestions! I will for sure be back!
Awesome coffee & great flavor combos. Service is excellent!
Had a wonderful experience ,    fantastic  customer service.   Love this coffee shop.

I love trying new privately owned cafes, but this one just was not the same. Customer service was ... blah at best. Not rude but no conversation no sense of excitement or enjoyment. The coffee unfortunately tasted like gas station coffee. I saw the guy pull espresso shots, so I was very surprised at the gas station taste. Unfortunately don't think I will be trying this place again. Definitely needs to engage with customers more to keep the business going long term. One bad coffee can be forgiven by a personable barista experience but that wasn't found here.
I have tried so many coffees around this area.  Tried their coffee today and shouldve got the large, didnt expect it to tastes so good.  I will be back soon. Service was awesome as well. Thanks!
It's such a nice,cozy place to have a cup of coffee and just chill. The service was friendly, and the iced latte was excellent.
Got their version of a caramel frappe, it was great. Got one of their pastries, very yummy. They were also very understanding of my uncles dietary restrictions.
Hands down Ten(10) Stars all day long! Super friendly staff and awesome coffee! Plays Christian music which I love and treats you better than family!! I will be back for sure!
best coffee in monroe + friendly staff. it's also super cute inside. I can't believe i didn't hear about it sooner! super underrated. i like all the unique flavors.
Great little coffee shop and friendly staff. The large is a 20 oz.
Had a coffee date. Very nice , comfy place to have conversations. Space is limited. Go during non busy hours

KB's has excellent coffee and espresso-based drinks as well as assorted pastries and muffins. I'd you're willing to try something new, ask for Puppy Love with vanilla cold foam. It's amazing!

The atmosphere is friendly and the space is cozy, with several separate spaces to relax and chat, and a couple of tables if you need to get some work done.

The owner is friendly and an excellent barista with a large variety of available flavor combinations, including an impressive number of sugar free options. If you like iced coffee, be sure to ask for coffee cubes instead of regular ice. I love them.

My wife and I stop in here at least once a week. We love it.
it is my morning place to enjoy a coffee and wifi and meet people. sometimes in the afternoon for tea and conversation always learn from others even when not in agreement. just love it.
Excellent coffee and even better service

Great place to chill- excellent coffee with so many options and flavors! Also teas, pastries, cookies, and a drive-thru!! Owner is ready and willing to make whatever combination you like  (including sugar-free!)

So glad we've found this local coffee shop with a great customer service and absolutely delicious coffee, and sweets. Inside the coffee shop is a very cozy and relaxing atmosphere. Me and my husband have enjoyed it very much. We would  definitely want to come here again.

I've gone here twice now and both times have been bad experiences. The first time I ordered a hot latte and I received a mocha that had so much chocolate in it it was basically a hot chocolate. The second time I went I ordered an iced oat milk latte and I received the most watered down iced coffee imaginable with no oat milk in it, pretty sure it did not contain espresso either. 2 bad experiences, won't be returning.
Cozy little corner with great conversation and coffee. Wonderful owners capable of creating culinary crafts you will crave!
This is a warm, inviting coffee shop with friendly owners and delicious coffee!

Excellent service
Amazing coffee

Me and my boyfriend came here for the first time and it was super adorable and cozy inside ! They had cinnamon roll cupcakes and they were delicious! The workers were also really nice! Definitely coming back!
Nice place to start yours day.! Go there
Come here every morning for a caramel macchiato. Great service and customers alike!!

This little coffee shop has a drive thru as well, which is awesome! I went in this time. Lots of spaces for parking as it is on the end of a strip mall. What a great atmosphere! There are places for group chats and a place in the back of you need more quiet. Their coffee menu is very fun. I did not have food so i can't comment on that. I had one of their fun coffees. It was enjoyable. I will definitely return to this coffee shop. It can be confusing about the name. KB's is on the door, but the sign on the building says Hazel's. Great place!
Baked item is what you would expect. The customer service is outstanding though and the coffee was made just the way I like it.
cute little corner coffee shop, atmosphere is so welcoming
Enjoyed the blended chai latte with whip cream and a slice of chocolate cake. I will certainly be back. Always friendly staff which makes the whole experience better.

The coffee is fresh and delicious, with a variety of options. Caleb was extremely friendly, and there are cozy seating areas to suit down and enjoy a conversation or read a book. Didn't bring a book? Not a problem. They have a little free book exchange,
Great friendly service and the coffee was better than Starbucks.  I'll be back!
The smoothies here are delicious + made with clean ingredients!  The new owners were super nice. Great vibe & fun decor!
The La la lavender white chocolate cold brew is amazing!!
My favorite coffee house in Monroe. Super friendly staff and unique menu.
Hazel's is an underrated gem. Their flavors are absolutely delicious, and they offer large sizes. I prefer Hazel's over any other coffee in the area. I only wish they were open later.
Coffee is delicious and the environment smells like vanilla. Just feels good.
Great place to relax, meet and greet, grab a coffee to go. Plenty of space.

Another quaint coffee shop find with open floorplan done "living room" style with couches and chairs throughout space.  It's a whole family affair as I met with the husband and wife owner team and their children.  Neat find at the corner of the shopping center.
Just came from Hazel's coffee shop first time there and the vibe is beautiful, I met the owner and she is so down to earth. The coffee is delicious . I will be back weekly!
The best coffee in town!

Hazel's coffee is the best in town.  I absolutely love their flavored coffees.  I would recommend their coffee over Dunkin or Starbucks any day.  Absolutely the best!  And the people there are the friendliest people you'll meet.
Love this place I've been stopping the past few morning there they only ones that can get my coffee perfect I found my new coffee shop  Thanks
Good local place to get a coffee or a tea and some baked items.

I have followed this business on Facebook for a while simply because of their humor. I finally stopped by 2 weeks go and grabbed an iced mocha coffee, it was delicious and under $4! You can't beat the price and the guy working the window was over the top friendly. You can't beat seeing a happy face serving you your order.
While I found Evanescence to be an interesting radio choice for 730 am at a coffee shop the actual product was just fine
As soon as I walked in there was a peace met with a great welcome! I got a coffee with Carmel and soy milk. It's absolutely delicious!
Chocolate raspberry coffee is scrumptious
I love that they listen to my left wing philosophy

Every coffeehouse I go to that offers lavender flavor, I'll try it. I get iced lavender vanilla lattes. I had one at hazels today, and it was absolutely perfect. The best one I've had so far. Not too sweet but perfectly delicious. I had it with half-and-half which is also how I always take my coffee. You have to try hazels coffeehouse in Monroe. It's locally owned, so you'll be supporting your neighbor!
Great tasting coffee and nice staff
Good iced lattes!
I love the convenience of Hazel's Coffee drive thru!  The coffee is perfect every time.
Come for a cup of cheer, made your way, and stay a few and bend an ear... sarcasm and opinions welcome!
Awesomeness
A very nice place, great frappes

We loved this place. We were looking for a coffee shop on the way to Charlotte.  The GPS took us here. What a fortunate turn of events. The owners were delightful. It was awesome. Coffee drinks were great. Plus, it was like we walked into a room of friends. Loved it so much. We will be back. You cant go wrong at this delightful place.
Great coffee, even better people!
I tried a cup of coffee from this place for the first time and ....it was so delicious, I wish that I could give this place 10 stars
Ist time here...but it want b my last. And it's close to home...#LifeofMrJava

Recently found this place and I love it! Good coffee and convenient drive thru. My only complaints are I wish you had more weekend hours, and I don't love the styrofoam cups that iced drinks come in (can't be recycled).
That being said I'll definitely be a regular customer!
Delicious coffee and slushies too can't wait to try the pina colada they also have a little drive-thru this is a great little coffee shop
It was good but some nats was buzzing around me and my friend heads.
The staff is awesome and the drinks are delicious and hilariously named. Best coffee shop in Monroe!

great coffee. great coffee cake. great atmosphere (even tho I just do take away) just really great!
(spectacular service even!!!)

and a drive thru
Great atmosphere,  from high octane to melow. Either bring a friend or go and make a friend.
Our first, but not our last, time. Excellent coffee (dark roast) and coffee cake muffin. Thanks!
Always friendly and welcoming staff. Wide variety of drink choices.

If you all don't know Hazel's moved in the plaza where the old Harris Teeeter was in Monroe. They were extremely sweet and kind and their coffee was amazing, so many different combinations to choose from.

Asked the barista to just make me anything, and she made me a delicious drink. Great baked goods and a greater atmosphere. Everyone inside had a big smile sharing laughs, customers and workers. Go here!

Been there several times. From the great service you will receive to the quiet quaint coffee shop setting where you can sit enjoy your coffee and strike up a conversation with the other patronages a true "Cheers" atmosphere.....
Had an excellent chai latte with cream.  Yum!
Best stop before work!! Love the Klatch! :)
One of the best coffee shops in the area
Very good coffee!
Good coffee and friendly staff but fairly dirty restroom.

I stopped in to get coffee while on a long trip. I was kind of shocked to see an actual non-chain cafe. This place feels like the set of a tv show. All the customers seemed to be having a single conversation when i walked in. Coffee pretty good. The owner hand writes witty slogans on all the cups.
N E A T

The Russian Milk Maid Latte is Great! Not too sweet, but has a prefect blend of white chocolate and irish cream and the coffee has good strength to it yet not too bold. The staff is also nice. Thumbs up for me :)
Amazing hot chocolate
I love this place! I go out of my way when traveling to S.C. from Michigan to go here. The coffees have a hint of hazelnut flavor and is so good!
Great little coffee shop with a welcoming atmosphere. The staff was friendly friendly. Would recommend for some great coffee.
Hazels is where the "Klatch Life" is in Full Effect in Monroe! The Only spot in Union County I can order a "cuban" and get it Miami Style!!

Dirty chai tea (iced)!!! Thank you Hazel house coffee!!! This place has everything you need in the morning to get through your day .
5 star and over!!!
Owner is an amazingly nice guy! Ambience is cozy and relaxing.

The coffee shop is cozy and clean. Bathroom is well-maintained. As far as drinks go, the beverages do not disappoint. I do wish they sell more types of cookies and bread, the selection needs to be wider.
Awesome,  great tasty Latte Mocha's!
Great atmosphere and friendly staff!
Really cool laid back place for coffee. Coffee was very good and their other drinks are delicious as well.
Great place to chill. Good coffee and pastries. Friendly staff.
Always the best time. Great conversation. Awesome atmosphere.
Now this is a chill coffee house!!!
Fantastic espresso. Friendly family feeling. Very nice people. Awesome vibe. Very glad that I stopped by.
A haven of civil discourse in the midst of a broken world circling the drain. And the cold brew is good too.
Good and warming place to be.
Best cofee in the east side of the city.

Great stuff.
"Water is the most essential element of life, because without water, you can't make coffee."
I love you

Good coffee and friendly, helpful barista! The pastries are okay, but I would love a better selection...or something unique. I didn't use my computer there, but I did notice that they've provided wifi and plenty of outlets. I would go more often if they had better weekend hours.
Great atmosphere, nice and quiet. Perfect to enjoy coffee
Awesome Cappuccino!
Best friend works here (it's their family business). Everyone is friendly and food is amazing. Highly recommend their smoothies (orgasmic).
Great service, kind staff, nice atmosphere! Oh and great coffee!
Great coffee. Amazing staff. Very cute and quaint

The moment I stepped into Hazel's, it quickly became one of my favorite coffee houses in Monroe. Both the owner and patrons greeted me with smiles and made me feel very welcome. I ordered the Monster Mash, which is a frozen blended drink with cookie pieces crushed up, tasted amazing, especially on Halloween.
I walked in looking to kill some time and get a coffee but I walked out with a fantastic original tasting beverage, three new friends, and a new coffeehouse to hangout at. When you go, tell Frank I said hey!
Good place to get some work done. Wifi. Very clean and low key. Average prices.
I love the people, and how they care about the coffee. It's good to small businesses do well. Stop in and say hello to them.
Awesome service.. Great Coffee and drinks..
